sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1649002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Red light sensor with TetR not gate and GFP reporter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: As the transcription from the red light sensor is repressed by the function of red light and activated by dark, we use a not gate, repressor TetR and tetr operator to ensure the system is activated by red light.GFP can be used to test whether the circuit works.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Yang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: kit plate
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: To test the efficiency of the red light sensor.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cph8
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is identical to BBa_I15010, the cph8 red light sensor. We were unable to transform BBa_I15010 from the the 2011 iGEM distribution kit. PCR attempts using VF2 and VR failed to amplify any DNA from the well sample. In the end, we chose to amplify cph8 from Jeffrey Tabor's pJT122 plasmid provided by Chris Voigt. The cph8 in pJT122 contained an internal PstI site, which was removed by point-mutagenesis. The resultant DNA sequence is identical to that of BBa_I15010.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lei Sun
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Jeffrey Tabor's pJT122 plasmid
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The source DNA (pJT122) contained illegal restriction site (PstI) that had to be removed.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: OmpR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Positively regulated, OmpR-controlled promoter. This promoter is taken from the upstream region of ompC. Phosphorylated OmpR binds to the three operator sites and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: NC_000193 E. coli K12
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The promoter includes the three OmpR binding sites: C1, C2, and C3. The promoter starts at -107 and goes up to the transcriptional start site at +1.
An alternate version, BBa_R0083, cuts out the C2 and C3 sites.
The efficacy of this promoter versus the truncated ompC upstream region (BBa_R0083) or the ompF upstream region (BBa_R0084) is currently unknown.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetR
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the TetR protein without the Ribosome Binding Site. Modified with an LVA tail for rapid degradation of the protein and faster fall time for the emission. TetR binds to the pTet regulator (BBa_R0040). aTc (anhydrotetracycline) binds to TetR and inhibits its operation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Elowitz, M. B. Transport, Assembly, and Dynamics in Systems of Interacting Proteins. Thesis, Princeton Univ., Princeton (1999)

BBa_C0040 TetR Protein is based on the TetR sequence from Elowitz's repressilator. It has been modified to include a rapid degradation LVA tail, and includes the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites. The RBS has been removed. The stop codon has been changed from TAA to a double stop codon TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
